Pattern - Cyclic Sort

Code-

var findErrorNums = function(nums) {
    let n = nums.length;
    let freq = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);

    for (let num of nums) {
        freq[num]++;
    }

    let duplicate = -1, missing = -1;

    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        if (freq[i] === 2) duplicate = i;
        if (freq[i] === 0) missing = i;
    }

    return [duplicate, missing];
};




Problem-
Array contains numbers from 1 to n
One number is duplicated
One number is missing
Return: [duplicate, missing]
Pattern
Hashing / Counting
Key Idea
Track frequency of each number
Find:
number with freq = 2 → duplicate
number with freq = 0 → missing

-Steps
Create frequency array of size n+1
Traverse nums:
Increment count for each number
Traverse 1 to n:
If freq[i] == 2 → duplicate
If freq[i] == 0 → missing
